The SwitchPath cat-back system from @awetuningofficial offer two distinct tones in one package. This kit unleashes a signature soundtrack out of the Z06, whether the valves are open or closed, thanks to its specifically tuned straight-through mufflers and precision-engineered x-pipe. It’s aggressive with the valves closed, and viscous with them open–just how a high-revving flat-plane V8 should be. Well-collected and comfortable when cruising (like stock), a riot when ripping, all controlled via the factory controls. If you’re planning on high flow cats, proceed with confidence as we engineered our mufflers to be fully capable of controlling those harsh frequencies. There’s also no need for a post-install visit to your local dealer for a valve relearn. Once it’s on, you’re clear for takeoff. Not only does the SwitchPath feature tier 1 OEM-supplied valves, included in every kit is a set of machined aluminum brackets to accommodate the factory valve motors and their factory linkage, keeping them away from the hot exhaust prolonging the lifespan of the electronics. Further, these valves won’t rattle a year later after installation – others on the market will. Two machined aluminum heat shields bolt-on to the Z06’s bumper using factory mounting points allowing the exhaust to shine through the mesh while protecting the inside of the bumper. No exhaust wraps that will inevitably become waterlogged and cause damage to whatever lies underneath. This exhaust system sheds 15lbs off your car’s weight getting rid of that heavy factory system. Topped off with quad 4.5” double-walled slash-cut tips exclusively in diamond black that fill the Z06’s bumper perfectly without any need for additional filler. The SwitchPath system does not interfere with any factory emissions equipment, so it is 100% emissions friendly, and a lifetime warranty comes standard. 😎

We built this truck at the beginning of 2020 for our good friend @jsimmons_94 . Then, wrapped it in a sweet dark gold color at the end of 2020. A few weeks ago it came back to us for a new phase of life.⁠
Our team stripped everything off and spent countless hours rebuilding it from the ground up with new equipment and new design ideas. We had the @anylevellift powder coated in Prismatic Illusion Red. Several other components, including the @road_armor bumpers and headache rack, were powder coated Dark Blue. Our wrap team got to work with the @averydennison Gloss Smoky Blue. They pulled the bed and wrapped the whole truck including the faces of the bumpers and headache rack creating a cool two tone look with the dark blue powder coating. While the wrap team was wrapping and the mechanical team was working on the lift, our 12 volt guys were installing a RGBW rock light system that works in unison with or separate from the interior lighting, a train horn system, smoked Morimoto taillights, all new light bars, and custom made illuminated “JS” badges front and rear with the custom “SIMMONS” appliqué on the tailgate. They also installed and tuned a Helix audio package with Sony’s flagship 9500ES at the helm. Going the extra mile, they laid down three layers of @soundshield to combat road noise and fully harness the audio build’s power. Rounding out the interior, our upholstery department installed a custom diamond stitched Napa leather kit from @alealeather with the custom embroidered “JS” headrests. With the lift on and the rest of the truck wrapped up, the mechanic bay slapped on this nasty set of 26” @jtxforged wheels in a beautiful brushed finish with those badass custom “JS” floating center caps and wrapped in 40” @furytires.⁠
⁠
The whole team absolutely knocked this one out of the park and we are so proud of all the handwork and excellent teamwork that made this monster build happen!⁠
⁠

Upgrading your car's audio system? If so, don't overlook the importance of sound-deadening material! While it may not be the sexiest part of your installation, it can greatly impact the overall sound quality and listening experience.⁠
⁠
So, what exactly is sound-deadening material? It's essentially a type of insulation placed inside your car's doors, roof, and floor to reduce the amount of outside noise entering the cabin. This is important because external noise can interfere with the sound coming from your speakers, leading to a muddied or distorted sound.⁠
⁠
In addition to reducing external noise, sound-deadening material can also improve the overall acoustics of your car's interior. Reducing vibrations and echoing allows your speakers to produce a cleaner, more accurate sound. This means that you'll be able to hear more detail in your music, from the subtle nuances of a singer's voice to the intricate instrumentation of Taylor Swift's new album.⁠
⁠
Another benefit of using sound-deadening material is that it can improve the overall comfort of your car. By reducing outside noise, it can make your car's cabin a quieter, more peaceful place to be. This is especially important if you spend a lot of time commuting or taking road trips, as it can help reduce the stress and fatigue that can come with long hours on the road.⁠
⁠

When it comes to achieving the ultimate sound quality in your car audio system, tuning is absolutely essential. And with the help of a Digital Signal Processor (DSP) and Real-Time Analyzer (RTA), we are able to tune systems with a level of detail and precision that will blow your mind.⁠
⁠
A DSP allows you to manipulate the audio signal in your car to achieve the best possible sound. You can adjust EQ, time alignment, crossover points, and more. But to truly optimize your system, you'll need to use an RTA.⁠
⁠
An RTA is a powerful tool that analyzes the audio signal in real time, giving us a visual representation of the sound waves in your car. This allows us to identify and correct any issues with the sound quality, such as peaks or dips in frequency response.⁠
⁠
The process of tuning your car audio system with a DSP and RTA involves a series of tests and adjustments. First, we measure the frequency response of each speaker in your car using an RTA. This gives a baseline understanding of how the speakers are performing.⁠
⁠
Next, we use the DSP to adjust the EQ, time alignment, and crossover points to optimize the sound quality. After each adjustment, we re-measure the frequency response with the RTA to ensure we're on the right track.⁠
⁠
By using an RTA in conjunction with a DSP, we can achieve a level of precision tuning that's simply not possible by ear alone. We're able to see exactly how the audio signal is behaving in your car and make adjustments accordingly.⁠
⁠
But why is tuning so important? When your car audio system is properly tuned, every note, every beat, every instrument comes through with crystal clarity. You'll hear details in your music that you never knew were there.⁠
⁠
So if you're serious about achieving the best possible sound quality in your car audio system, talk to one of our knowledgeable salesmen about getting a DSP in your system and having it tuned by a car audio master like Ray here. 💪⁠
